==English==

===Etymology===
After '''Hendrik Von Prehn''', Dutch colonial governor
*Note: This was the first mineral to be named after a person

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''prehnite'''

#{{mineralogy}} a [[mineral]], a basic [[calcium]], [[aluminium]] and [[iron]] [[aluminosilicate]], which occurs in [[stalagtitic]] [[aggregate]]s or [[curved]] [[crystal]]s